Bermuda's national drink, codified by the Outerbridge family at the Swizzle Inn around 1932 and built around Gosling's Black Seal — the dark molasses character of that rum is what differentiates it from a generic Caribbean swizzle. Often scaled up and made in a pitcher with a swizzle stick for sharing.

In a #pitcher{} or #shaker{} filled with ice combine @Gosling's Black Seal rum{2%oz}, @fresh orange juice{2%oz}, @pineapple juice{2%oz}, @grenadine{1%dash}, and @Angostura bitters{1%dash}.

Churn with a @swizzle stick{} (rolling it between the palms) until the drink is foamy and the outside of the pitcher is frosted.

Pour into a #double old-fashioned glass{} filled with ice.

Garnish with a @half orange slice{1}, a @pineapple stick{1}, and a @maraschino cherry{1}.
